WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Mirror geometry demo.
X is self-reflection length in the mirror.

00:00:02.800 --> 00:00:05.600
Y is reflected wall-height segment in the mirror.
Use similar triangles and virtual-image distance.

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:08.000
For this worksheet: X = 75 cm, Y = 60 cm.
If distance d changes, X stays fixed while Y grows with d.
